The paper deals with the problem of graph clustering, which is a common task in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The authors also mention the use of integer programming, which is a topic in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), and the potential relevance of their approach to other combinatorial problems, which could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) or graph theory (cs.GR).
